## 2. Quick Start (5 Minutes)

This is the fastest path to get the entire system running from scratch.

### Step 1: Clone Repository

```bash
git clone <repository-url> && cd Online_Judge
```

### Step 2: Start Infrastructure Services

Use Docker Compose to start PostgreSQL and Redis:

```bash
docker compose up -d postgres redis
```

Wait for health checks to pass (approximately 30 seconds):

```bash
docker compose ps postgres redis
```

Confirm both containers show `healthy` in the Status column.

### Step 3: Start Backend API Service

```bash
cd backend
cargo run --bin api
```

First-time compilation takes several minutes (subsequent incremental builds will be much faster). When successfully started, you should see output similar to:

```
INFO api: Connecting to database...
INFO api: Database connection pool created
INFO api: Running embedded database migrations...
INFO api: Database migrations complete
INFO api: Redis connection pool created
INFO api: Starting server on 0.0.0.0:3000
INFO api: Server listening on 0.0.0.0:3000
```

The API service automatically runs database migrations on startup (see Section 4), no manual intervention needed.

### Step 4: Start Frontend Development Server

Open a new terminal window:

```bash
cd frontend
npm ci
npm run dev
```

The Vite development server starts on port 5173 and automatically proxies `/api` requests to the backend `localhost:3000`.

### Step 5: Access Application

Open in browser:

```
http://localhost:5173
```

### Step 6: Load Demo Data (Optional)

```bash
bash scripts/bootstrap_demo.sh
```

This script inserts demo organization ("Demo School"), test users, sample problems, and contest data into the database. The script supports idempotent execution and can be safely run repeatedly. After loading completes, use these test accounts (password: `admin123` for all):

| Email | Username | Role | Purpose |
|-------|----------|------|---------|
| `admin@example.com` | 1001 | root (admin) | Admin backend, user management |
| `student1@example.com` | 2001 | student | Submit code, participate in contests |
| `student2@example.com` | 2002 | student | Second student test account |
| `teacher@example.com` | 3001 | teacher | Create problems, manage classes |

